# C2 Server вҖ” Security Hardening Reference

## 1. Cryptography

### Before
A single Fernet key was hardcoded in both [server.py](file:///c:/Malware-Dev/C2%20server/server.py) and [agent.py](file:///c:/Malware-Dev/C2%20server/agent.py):

```python
SECRET_KEY = b'B9gEUjAh8XJvCR5O0-ukDOxEczt3YXDzkeL1wco73cE='
cipher = Fernet(SECRET_KEY)
```

**Impact:** Extract that key from any agent binary вҶ’ decrypt all historical and future traffic, impersonate any agent, forge task results.

### After вҖ” RSA-bootstrapped Per-Agent Keys

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Agent
    participant S as Server

    A->>S: GET /pub
    S-->>A: RSA-2048 public key (PEM)
    Note over A: Generate random Fernet key
    Note over A: RSA-OAEP encrypt it with server pubkey
    A->>S: POST /api/register {agent_id, enc(session_key), timestamp_ms}
    Note over S: RSA-decrypt вҶ’ store session_key in SQLite
    S-->>A: {token: HMAC(OPERATOR_TOKEN, agent_id)}
    Note over A,S: All future traffic encrypted with this agent's key only
```

- Server generates a **fresh RSA-2048 key pair at every startup** вҖ” keys are never written to disk.
- Each agent generates its own **random Fernet key** (AES-128-CBC + HMAC-SHA256) on startup.
- The agent wraps its Fernet key with **RSA-OAEP-SHA256** before sending it вҖ” only the server's private key can unwrap it.
- **No shared secret exists.** Compromise one agent вҶ’ only that agent's session key is exposed.

---

## 2. Authentication & Replay Protection

### Before
```python
headers = {
    "Authorization": f"Bearer {AGENT_ID}",   # just a label вҖ” no verification
}
```

### After вҖ” Per-Request HMAC

Every beacon and result upload carries three headers:

| Header | Value |
|---|---|
| `X-Agent-Id` | Agent UUID |
| `X-Timestamp` | Unix milliseconds |
| `X-Signature` | `HMAC-SHA256(session_key, "{agent_id}:{timestamp_ms}")` |

The server recomputes the HMAC using the stored session key and rejects anything that doesn't match. Since only that agent and the server know the session key, no one else can produce a valid signature.

**Replay protection вҖ” two layers:**
1. **Timestamp window:** requests with a timestamp more than Вұ60 seconds from server time are instantly rejected.
2. **Nonce cache:** the exact [(agent_id, timestamp_ms)](file:///c:/Malware-Dev/C2%20server/agent.py#239-254) pair is stored in memory for 120 seconds. A captured-and-replayed packet within the window is still rejected.

### Operator vs. Agent Split

`/api/push` requires a completely separate credential:

```
Authorization: Bearer <OPERATOR_TOKEN>
```

`OPERATOR_TOKEN` is loaded **only from an environment variable** вҖ” never hardcoded, never sent to agents. A compromised agent cannot push tasks to other agents.

---

## 3. Database вҖ” SQLite Schema

`c2.db` is created automatically in the same directory as [server.py](file:///c:/Malware-Dev/C2%20server/server.py).

```
в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ  agents                                         в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  agent_id   TEXT  PK   вҖ” UUID                   в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  session_key BLOB      вҖ” Fernet key (plaintext)  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  token      TEXT       вҖ” HMAC-derived            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  registered REAL       вҖ” Unix timestamp          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  last_seen  REAL       вҖ” updated on each beacon  в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ

в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ  tasks                                          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  id         INT   PK   вҖ” auto-increment          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  agent_id   TEXT       вҖ” FK вҶ’ agents             в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  payload    TEXT       вҖ” JSON task dict          в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  status     TEXT       вҖ” pending | delivered     в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  created_at REAL                                 в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ

в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
в”Ӯ  results                                        в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ  в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  id         INT   PK                            в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  agent_id   TEXT                                в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  output     TEXT       вҖ” shell output etc.       в”Ӯ
в”Ӯ  received_at REAL                               в”Ӯ
в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
```

**Why it matters vs. `tasks = {}`:**
- Server restart вҶ’ agents and queued tasks survive. No re-registration required.
- Tasks move from `pending` вҶ’ `delivered` when a beacon picks them up вҖ” you can track what has actually been sent.
- `results` is a permanent audit log of everything agents reported back.
- The `c2.db` file is a single portable file вҖ” easy to back up or move between machines.

